 ## Unreleased
 
+- Added depth-2 composer quote verification reports (frac-0045): `my-claw/tools/composer_quote_verify.py` now exposes a frozen `QuoteVerificationReport` plus typed helpers `build_quote_verification_report`, `summarize_quote_verification_report`, `render_quote_verification_lines`, and `quote_verification_exit_code` around the existing hardware-free known-room/self-quote smoke path. The report captures descriptor identity/tags, requested/captured piece counts, song ids, match details, overlap, score, and status while preserving `trigger_composer_pieces`, `find_motif_tag_match`, and the CLI's existing success/failure output and exit codes. `tests/test_composer_quote_verify_depth.py` pins the end-to-end report, JSON-safe summary, CLI line rendering, failure-status exit mapping, and fractal depth >= 2; original composer quote, sample capture, self-listener, and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
+
 - Added depth-2 hook schema rewriter (frac-0044): `rewrite_hook.py` is now an importable module with a frozen `HookRewriteResult` dataclass plus typed helpers `apply_field_renames`, `migrate_file`, `apply_hook_rewrites`, and `main`, sourced from a canonical `HOOK_FIELD_RENAMES` table (`("hook_type", "hook_class")`, `("rhythm_cell", "rhythm")`) and `HOOK_TARGET_FILES` listing the five SenseWeave files the original one-shot script wrote to. The previous body of unconditional regex/`str.replace` calls — which left an already-migrated tree corrupted with duplicate dataclass fields and a broken `return HookProfile(...)` block when re-run — is replaced by an idempotent rename: `apply_field_renames` is pure string-in/string-out, `migrate_file` only writes when the produced text differs from disk and reports `existed`/`changed`, missing files report `existed=False` without raising, and `apply_hook_rewrites(root)` walks `HOOK_TARGET_FILES` in declared order returning one `HookRewriteResult` per target. `main()` prints a `rewrote`/`unchanged`/`missing` line per result and exits 0; `if __name__ == "__main__"` is preserved. `tests/test_rewrite_hook_depth.py` pins canonical-rename, idempotency, write-on-change, no-op-on-migrated-file, missing-file handling, declared-order tree migration, end-to-end idempotency on a migrated tree, the canonical rename table, and fractal depth >= 2; senseweave hook tests remain regression coverage.
 
 - Added depth-2 PromptClaw artifact run reports (frac-0043): `promptclaw/artifacts.py` now exposes frozen `ArtifactFileStatus` and `ArtifactRunReport` dataclasses plus `ArtifactManager.build_run_report()` so callers can summarize expected run files, present/missing counts, missing file names, event count, and latest event type from the canonical `ProjectPaths.run_layout()` and existing event log. Existing artifact write helpers, `read_events()`, JSONL event shape, and on-disk `.promptclaw/runs/<run-id>/` filenames are preserved. `tests/test_promptclaw_artifacts_report.py` pins written-artifact summaries, JSON-safe report output, and fractal depth >= 2; existing artifact depth tests and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
